However, we are closely following the market and we are ready to adapt immediately if we decide that the time is flawless for unlocking. However, we are closely following the market and we are ready to adapt immediately if we decide that the time is flawless for unlocking. Again, we think we are very close to a certain exchange listing and the market is quite twitchy at the moment, so we don't want to make any rash decisions. We will monitor the situation closely over the next week and will update the community if there are any changes to our decision. If we decide to unlock, it won't happen overnight as we will make an annoucement and set a date so FT holders can prepare. That's it for now regarding this matter. Additionally, we will be in Estonia from the 6th to the 9th of May, taking care of some business and legal matters. In the meantime, our full focus is still on the development of TokenGen 2.0. Cheers to everyone!

Author: n00b3rt
Title: 📌 [ANN] 🔥 [TGE] 🔴 FABRIC TOKEN 🔴 DRAG-AND-DROP SMART CONTRACTS 🔥
Body: Someone asked me the same thing recently and basically, here's my response (from Telegram) as to why we are not using a third-party to audit our smart contracts: Quote First of all, between us all on the Fabric Token team, we have a lot of programming experience, especially our CTO. And second, our smart contracts include only simple token and crowdsale functionality. These are already well known in the industry and the methods used in them have been audited and used are re-used over and over again. A third-party audit is needed once custom business logic enters the scene. So if a project needs smart contracts for a freelancer website for example, or for a marketplace, then they will have additional smart contracts that are not of the standard token and crowdsale functionality. Then, it is a really good idea to get these smart contracts audited by someone else, capable of doing it right.

Body: Sorry, there won't be alpha testing. Only public beta versions of all our products.  Quote from: nicolasbit on December 30, 2017, 07:21:19 AM Hello. How many tokens will be available during the ICO? Tokens available for sale will be 80 million. For more info about the FT ICO, refer to this page: https://fabrictoken.io/token-sale/  Quote from: devilini on December 30, 2017, 08:12:49 AM The problem with most ERP systems is an inability to configure them for the needs of the enterprise dynamically. How Fabric is going to solve this problem? DApp Workbench will allow the development, monitoring and deployment of smart contract/business processes in real-time, thus allowing businesses to improve their processes and automation.  Quote from: Ackedy on December 30, 2017, 10:02:06 AM Good afternoon. Has pre -sale already been completed? We won't be holding a pre-sale. The project is already well-funded thus we don't need a pre-sale or a secondary sale.  Quote from: nextwalker on December 30, 2017, 10:03:29 AM ETH blockchain was overloaded recently and partially suspended its operation. How do you plan to protect your networks from a similar scenario? The Fabric Token is based on the ETH blockchain, but it can be migrated to a different blockchain if needed. DApp Workbench works with either blockchains of the client itself or the public Ethereum blockchain. This question is only relevant to the Fabric Store. The idea is to use a permissioned blockchain, based on Hyperledger Fabric, as it has multiple features to provide isolation and means to mitigate large variety of attacks. We will research that topic further once TokenGen and DApp Workbench are ready to support user-contributed extensions.  Quote from: Immer on December 30, 2017, 10:13:51 AM Good afternoon. How many blockchain platforms will your app support? In my opinion - the more of them, the better it is. We have planned to support multiple blockchain platforms for both TokenGen and DApp Workbench. As a start we will target Ethereum and in the case for the DApp Workbench we also target Hyperledger Fabric. Once those capabilities are mature, we can easily add more platforms in our "expansion" epic (epic as in SCRUM).  Quote from: reallyhawk on December 30, 2017, 10:23:35 AM Why did you choose BPMN 2.0 exactly? I’ve heard that its maintenance is very expensive. We chose a subset of the BPMN 2.0 specification that will allow workflow automation, in addition to that, not all activities are relevant for processes running on a blockchain.  Quote from: slavonicpl on December 30, 2017, 10:29:57 AM Does your team have experts who understand how blockchain technology is developing? If you anticipate the direction, you can significantly increase the value of the token. Yes we do. Our entire team has a great understanding of blockchain technology and each brings a unique view of the industry. If there's an opportunity, we are sure to spot it right away.  Quote from: termonator61 on December 30, 2017, 10:30:57 AM Hello. I got interested in your project, but first I’d like to learn: how much will one transaction cost me in the framework of DApp Workbench? DApp Workbench will support, as a start, the Ethereum blockchain and Hyperledger Fabric. So, a transaction will cost the standard ETH gas cost if the smart contracts are deployed on the Ethereum blockchain, and if they are deployed on a Hyperledger blockchain, the transaction cost will be literally 0 due to Hyperledger being a private blockchain for businesses.

Today there’re a lot of solutions of the day for transformation of the business from paper to digital form in the market. What is your ultimate advantage? Of course, it will cover a lot more use cases than that, but I just wanted to illustrate with your example. We just need to make a few design adjustments and test it out extensively to make sure there are not security bugs.   I will join bounty too. Good lck. Good luck to all fellow bounty participants. I hope we'll create a strong tightly-knit community over here and see the dev team push this project to success. I love dev-focused teams  nad I'm loving that we're from the same country Cheers mate!
